<div class="ds-eyebrow">Data visualization</div>
<h1 class="ds-title">Charts</h1>
<p class="ds-lede">On-brand chart specimens — pure HTML/CSS/inline-SVG, no chart library. Each maps its series colors (<code>--chart-1</code> / <code>--chart-2</code>) to the Curie brand tokens (purple + teal) and uses the system's typography and corner radii, so charts read as part of Curie. In-app the data would be bound with a chart library (e.g. Recharts); these show the target visual.</p>
<div class="ds-example-grid">
{% for c in chartsManifest.charts %}
  <a class="ds-component-card" href="/charts/{{ c.id }}/">
    <span class="cat">{{ c.category }}</span>
    <h3>{{ c.name }}</h3>
    <p>{{ c.purpose }}</p>
  </a>
{% endfor %}
</div>
